A Federal High Court sitting in Minna has struck out the case of financial misappropriation brought against the former governor of Niger State, Dr Mu’azu Babangida Aliyu, for lack of proper prosecution by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission ( EFCC). The court, presided over by Justice Aliyu Aminu Bappa, struck out the suit at the resumed sitting yesterday, when the case was called and the prosecuting counsel of the EFCC,  Kabir Latino, was not in court. He, however, was represented by one of the lawyers who told the court that he was in court to hold brief for his senior who could not make it due to some official engagement that took him out of office. Justice Aliyu had, at the resumed hearing into the matter 21st May, threatened to strike out the case if the prosecutor  from the legal unit of the EFCC is not prepared for the case. “From all indications, you people are not ready for the prosecution of this matter. I inherited this case, I started it denovo,” Justice Aliyu said. 